A former National Publicity Secretary of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Chief Olisa Metuh, has been released from the Kuje Custodial Centre. His release, on Thursday, followed the nullification of his seven-year jail term by the appellate court handed to him by Justice Okon Abang of the Federal High Court in Abuja. Justice Abang had on February 25, pronounced Metuh guilty on all counts of money laundering and sentenced him to seven years in prison. The Federal High Court, Abuja, on Thursday, admitted Metuh to a N250 million bail, which he met. The former PDP spokesman is standing trial for allegedly collecting N400 million meant for arms procurement from a former National Security Adviser, Col. Sambo Dasuki (retd). Vanguard News Nigeria The Chief Judge of the Federal Capital Territory High Court, Justice Ishaq Bello, yesterday, granted bail to the embattled National Publicity Secretary of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Chief Olisa Metuh, to the tune of N300million with two sureties in like sum. January 23, 2016 In "News" ABUJA â€” The Abuja Division of the Federal High Court, yesterday, granted bail to the embattled National Publicity Secretary of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Mr. Olisa Metuh, to the tune of N400 million. January 20, 2016 In "News" The Federal High Court sitting Abuja has granted bail to the embattled National Publicity Secretary of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Mr. Olisa Metuh, to the tune of N400million. January 19, 2016 In "News"